Features Supported in This BNF
Modules with explicit declarations

Multiple function clauses with guards (when)

Pattern matching in function parameters and case expressions

Basic arithmetic expressions with unary + and - operators

Function calls with arguments

Variables (capitalized, can contain letters/digits)

Literals: integer, float, string, atoms (quoted and unquoted)

Complex data types: lists, tuples, maps, binaries

Special Erlang data types: PIDs, Ports, References

Anonymous functions (fun ... end)

Control flow: if-else, case expressions with pattern matching

String concatenation via the space " " operator (in expressions, implicit in string handling)

Guard expressions in functions and if clauses

Quoted atoms supporting special characters

Bitstring syntax with size/type specifiers


